cs.CR, cs.IOT, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper primarily focuses on security and privacy concerns in the context of connected vehicles and proposes a formalized access control model to address these issues. 
2. cs.IOT (Internet of Things): The paper deals with the vehicular internet of things (IoT) domain and discusses the communication and interaction among various connected entities in this ecosystem. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the large amount of code and sensors involved in connected vehicles and discusses the implementation of the proposed access control model in the AWS cloud platform. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the use of cloud computing for implementing the proposed access control model and mentions the performance metrics of the implementation. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of dynamic groups for managing large numbers of smart entities and mentions the relevance of location and time-sensitive notification services to the consumers, which are related to systems and control.
